					Full Description



Thermon Group Holdings, Inc., incorporated on March 19, 2010, is a provider of engineered thermal solutions for process industries. The Company offers a range of products, such as heating cables, tubing bundles and control systems, and services, such as design optimization, engineering, and installation and maintenance services. The Company operates through four segments based on four geographic countries or regions: United States, Canada, Europe and Asia. The Company's thermal solutions, also referred to as heat tracing, provide an external heat source to pipes, vessels and instruments for the purposes of freeze protection, temperature and flow maintenance, environmental monitoring, and surface snow and ice melting.The Company offers a range of electric heat tracing cables, steam tracing components, tubing bundles, and instrument and control products, as well as various complementary product lines. The Company's product portfolio includes self-regulating and power limiting heating cables, which automatically change heat output as pipe temperature changes, as well as constant wattage heating cables; mineral insulated (MI) cable; skin effect trace heater; heat traced tube bundles for environmental gas sampling systems; heat transfer compounds and steam tracers for steam tracing solutions; control and monitoring systems for electric tracing of pipes, tanks, hoppers and instrument sampling systems; turnkey solutions that provide customers with solutions for heat tracing, including design, optimization, installation and ongoing maintenance; products and services, such as heating, sensing, monitoring, controlling and calibration tools, and temporary electric power distribution and lighting products used in energy infrastructure construction projects, and maintenance and turnaround projects.Electric Heat Tracing ApplicationsThe Company manufactures components of an electric heat tracing system, including heating cables, control and monitoring systems, and heating systems for tanks and hoppers. The Company also offers various electric heating cables, including conductive polymer self-regulating heating cables and power limiting cables. The Company's HTSX self-regulating heating cable is suitable for heat tracing applications involving crude oil and various chemicals. The TEK and HTEK series resistance, constant watt heating cables are used where circuit lengths exceed the limitations of parallel resistance heating cables. MIQ mineral insulated heating cables are used for high temperature maintenance, high temperature exposure and high watt density applications. MIQ cables are composed of a high nickel or chromium alloy sheath. The Company's ThermTrac system is designed to heat a pipeline of approximately 15 miles long from a single power point.Steam Heat TracingThe Company offers range of heat transfer compounds, as well as steam tracers and tubing bundles that provide its customers with steam tracing solutions. The Company's heat transfer compounds create a thermal connection between the heat tracing system and the process equipment.Temperature Controls and MonitoringThe Company supplies a range of control and monitoring products, from mechanical thermostats to microprocessor-based systems that control and monitor the status of electric heat tracing systems. The Company provides individual units for projects, as well as multi-point controllers that can be integrated into and communicate with a plant's central data management and control system. The Company offers a range of temperature control monitoring systems as part of its TraceNet family of controllers. TraceNet controllers allow the operator to assess operating control parameters and operating conditions throughout the heat tracing system network utilizing its TraceNet control solutions. The Company's controllers can communicate with approximately 4,090 controllers over 32 channels, allowing approximately 15,000 heat trace circuits to be monitored within the same network.InstrumentationThe Company is engaged in providing pre-insulated and heat-traced tubing bundles with accessories. The Company's range of products includes both electric and steam-heated bundles containing various types of tubing, such as copper, stainless steel and polymer.Hopper HeatingThe Company's product, HT Hopper Heating Module, is a self-contained heater designed for operation on surfaces prone to vibration. The HT Hopper Heating Module has various flow paths for electrical current.Turnkey ServicesThe Company provides customers with various solutions for their heat tracing needs. Its services include project planning, product supply, engineering services, system integration, installation, commissioning and maintenance.Design and Engineering ServicesThe Company offers heat tracing design and engineering services during every stage of a project. The Company provides design and engineering services to its customers through its staff of engineers and technicians.Sumac Temporary Power ProductsThe Company, through Sumac Fabrication Company Limited (Sumac), offers power distribution panels, master or slave sub-panels, power cords and lighting fixtures. Sumac's line of products and solutions are designed to provide a means of supplying temporary electrical power distribution and lighting at energy infrastructure facilities for construction, and during maintenance and turnaround projects at operating facilities. Sumac's products are sold to end users operating in various markets, including heavy industrial settings, oil and gas refining and upgrading, power generation plants, petrochemical production facilities and mining operations.The Company competes with Pentair plc.

