					Full Description



Thermon Group Holdings, Inc., incorporated on March 19, 2010, is a provider of engineered thermal solutions for process industries. The Company offers a range of products, such as heating cables, tubing bundles and control systems, and services, such as design optimization, engineering, and installation and maintenance services. The Company operates through four segments based on four geographic countries or regions: United States, Canada, Europe and Asia. The Company's thermal solutions, also referred to as heat tracing, provide an external heat source to pipes, vessels and instruments for the purposes of freeze protection, temperature and flow maintenance, environmental monitoring, and surface snow and ice melting.The Company offers a range of electric heat tracing cables, steam tracing components, tubing bundles, and instrument and control products, as well as various complementary product lines. The Company's product portfolio includes self-regulating and power limiting heating cables, which automatically change heat output as pipe temperature changes, as well as constant wattage heating cables; mineral insulated (MI) cable; skin effect trace heater; heat traced tube bundles for environmental gas sampling systems; heat transfer compounds and steam tracers for steam tracing solutions; control and monitoring systems for electric tracing of pipes, tanks, hoppers and instrument sampling systems; turnkey solutions that provide customers with solutions for heat tracing, including design, optimization, installation and ongoing maintenance; products and services, such as heating, sensing, monitoring, controlling and calibration tools, and temporary electric power distribution and lighting products used in energy infrastructure construction projects, and maintenance and turnaround projects.Electric Heat Tracing ApplicationsThe Company manufactures components of an electric heat tracing system, including heating cables, control and monitoring systems, and heating systems 