Thermon Group Holdings, Inc. Key Developments

Thermon Group Holdings, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jul 26, 2017
Jun 16 17
Thermon Group Holdings, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jul 26, 2017, at 11:30 Central Standard Time. Location: Houston Airport Marriott at George Bush Intercontinental 18700 John F. Kennedy Blvd Houston, TX 77032 United States Agenda: To elect as directors the eight nominees named in the proxy statement, each for a term of one year; to ratify the appointment of KPMG LLP as the company's independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending March 31, 2018; to approve, on a non binding advisory basis, the compensation of executive officers; to re-approve the material terms of the performance measures under the Thermon Group Holdings, Inc. 2012 Short-Term Incentive Plan; and to transact such other business that may properly come before the 2017 Annual Meeting and any postponement or adjournment thereof.


Thermon Group Holdings, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Year Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Revenue Guidance for Fiscal 2018
May 24 17
Thermon Group Holdings, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and year ended March 31, 2017. During the fourth quarter of 2017, the Company generated revenue of $67.6 million versus $72.3 million in fourth quarter of 2016, a decrease of $4.7 million or 7%. Net income attributable to Thermon and GAAP EPS were $3.3 million and $0.10 per fully diluted common share, respectively, compared to $3.2 million and $0.10 per fully diluted common share, respectively, in fourth quarter of 2016. After taking into account certain one-time charges, the company generated adjusted net income of $3.3 million and adjusted EPS of $0.10 per fully diluted common share compared to $6.5 million and $0.20 per fully diluted common share, respectively, in fourth quarter of 2016. Income before provision for taxes was $4,379,000 against $4,728,000 a year ago. EBITDA was $9,558,000 against $9,697,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $10,400,000 against $14,435,000 a year ago. Return on Equity was 13% against 20% a year ago. 



In fiscal 2017, the company generated revenue of $264.1 million compared to $281.9 million in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2016, a decrease of $17.8 million or 6%. Fiscal 2017 net income attributable to Thermon and GAAP earnings per share were $14.6 million and $0.45 per fully diluted common share, respectively, compared to $23.0 million and $0.71 per fully diluted common share, respectively, in fiscal 2016. After taking into account certain one-time charges, the Company generated adjusted net income in fiscal 2017 of $14.1 million and adjusted EPS of $0.43 per fully diluted common share compared to adjusted net income of $28.9 million and adjusted EPS of $0.89 per fully diluted common share, respectively, during fiscal 2016. Income before provision for taxes was $19,082,000 against $32,366,000 a year ago. EBITDA was $39,523,000 against $52,853,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $43,268,000 against $65,240,000 a year ago. Return on Equity was 14% against 23% a year ago. 


The company expects fiscal 2018 revenue to be flat to slightly down from fiscal 2017 levels.


Thermon Group Seeks Acquisitions 
May 24 17
Thermon Group Holdings, Inc. (NYSE:THR) announced that its balance sheet provides the company with ample capability to acquire strategic businesses, and our target debt-to-EBITDA is in the 2x to 3x range.


